00:29:58.570 --> 00:30:01.240
is going to be around
our unique selling points

00:30:01.240 --> 00:30:05.770
about how we express who
we are in the digital space

00:30:05.770 --> 00:30:07.960
so that our cells
are working 24/7

00:30:07.960 --> 00:30:13.810
on our behalf in other words,
perhaps, with our ethos

00:30:13.810 --> 00:30:15.590
interfacing with the world.

00:30:15.590 --> 00:30:18.530
And so when it
comes down to music,

00:30:18.530 --> 00:30:20.950
how do we present ourselves?

00:30:20.950 --> 00:30:23.080
We have a major problem
in the music industry

00:30:23.080 --> 00:30:27.730
whereby the commercial
music industry didn't adopt

00:30:27.730 --> 00:30:30.580
the technology of MP3
and didn't see Napster

00:30:30.580 --> 00:30:35.620
as this incredible, amazing
opportunity to go, wow,

00:30:35.620 --> 00:30:39.710
this is life changing for
musicians and the industry.

00:30:39.710 --> 00:30:42.190
Let's get on this and make
it something really great.

00:30:42.190 --> 00:30:44.815
And instead, they kind of went,
let's sweep it under the carpet

00:30:44.815 --> 00:30:46.567
and put people in jail.

00:30:46.567 --> 00:30:49.150
And really, just people wanted
to share music that they loved,

00:30:49.150 --> 00:30:50.860
and so what happened
was that you

00:30:50.860 --> 00:30:53.650
had a huge disassociation
from the music and the people

00:30:53.650 --> 00:30:54.460
that made it.

00:30:54.460 --> 00:30:56.410
Then it just never
managed to catch up,

00:30:56.410 --> 00:30:58.970
and the music industry has
been trying to catch up,

00:30:58.970 --> 00:31:01.120
and they're basically
firefighting every day

00:31:01.120 --> 00:31:04.810
as people try to innovate
on this very crooked kind

00:31:04.810 --> 00:31:08.570
of heavy, clunky industry.

00:31:08.570 --> 00:31:10.150
So there's thousands
of services,

00:31:10.150 --> 00:31:12.250
and I've spoken to
hundreds of them, who

00:31:12.250 --> 00:31:16.180
want to build new services
using existing music,

00:31:16.180 --> 00:31:19.270
but to reach that point where
they have the permission

00:31:19.270 --> 00:31:22.720
to do that to license the
music, it's just not viable.

00:31:22.720 --> 00:31:25.270
They have to raise so much
money with VC that it then

00:31:25.270 --> 00:31:28.270
only leaves little, tiny scraps
for the musicians in the end

00:31:28.270 --> 00:31:31.480
if any, and it's a
very lengthy process.

00:31:31.480 --> 00:31:34.300
And I just feel
more than ever we

00:31:34.300 --> 00:31:37.510
have an opportunity with
new technologies where

00:31:37.510 --> 00:31:40.900
we could create an
open database of works

00:31:40.900 --> 00:31:43.660
that the whole world could
come around and create

00:31:43.660 --> 00:31:48.010
this kind of Alexandria, this
library of content, whereby

00:31:48.010 --> 00:31:51.040
all of the music services,
the labels, the publishers,

00:31:51.040 --> 00:31:54.340
the collection societies, who
all have their own databases

00:31:54.340 --> 00:31:57.370
at the moment, costing
them huge amounts of money,

00:31:57.370 --> 00:32:00.130
that they have to keep
updated and verified

00:32:00.130 --> 00:32:01.460
and all that stuff.

00:32:01.460 --> 00:32:03.220
And they're all
incomplete, and they all

00:32:03.220 --> 00:32:04.390
compete with one another.

00:32:04.390 --> 00:32:05.200
BEN ARTHUR: Right

00:32:05.200 --> 00:32:06.900
IMOGEN HEAP: But
if that was just--

00:32:06.900 --> 00:32:08.390
just get rid of that.

00:32:08.390 --> 00:32:11.260
We don't need to have multiple
versions of the same thing,

00:32:11.260 --> 00:32:13.330
and all slightly different,
and all slightly bad.

00:32:13.330 --> 00:32:15.940
Let's just have-- let's
share into a space

00:32:15.940 --> 00:32:23.230
and contribute to that alive
kind of world of music,

00:32:23.230 --> 00:32:27.280
and data, and augment
what's already there

00:32:27.280 --> 00:32:30.470
into something that can be
tuned in to by all the services

00:32:30.470 --> 00:32:33.050
so they don't have to have
that weight on their back,

00:32:33.050 --> 00:32:33.695
basically.

