00:40:32.850 --> 00:40:35.760
And that's tiny amounts
to these other artists,

00:40:35.760 --> 00:40:38.480
but to them it could be like
50 quid, or 100 quid, or 1,000

00:40:38.480 --> 00:40:38.980
quid.

00:40:41.600 --> 00:40:45.060
So when they create that, we
want the Creative Passport

00:40:45.060 --> 00:40:48.570
to be able to enable individual
musicians to be able to author

00:40:48.570 --> 00:40:54.000
into and claim a way to kind of
point to this is how to pay me,

00:40:54.000 --> 00:40:55.610
or this is my
collection society.

00:40:55.610 --> 00:40:57.810
Well, this is actually
me, this missing bit here.

00:40:57.810 --> 00:40:59.770
So that we can tidy up
and do the job for them

00:40:59.770 --> 00:41:03.910
that they can't afford to do
because it's tiny amounts.

00:41:03.910 --> 00:41:06.238
So the majors like the
record side of things,

00:41:06.238 --> 00:41:07.280
because they don't have--

00:41:07.280 --> 00:41:12.170
yeah, ISRC, and your ISWC
are two codes that you have,

00:41:12.170 --> 00:41:14.400
your recording and
your publishing.

